caption: UPDATE: After my first experience with California Tortilla I spoke with a customer service rep and they sent me a $20 gift card. The second time our food was spot on. I got a a Korean BBQ burrito with pork and it was spicy and delicious. My wife and son also got meals but I can not recall what they ordered but they enjoyed their meals. Glad that the first bad experience was a fluke. I will try them again.  Ordered a take out meal for my wife, my son, and myself. My sons quesadilla was spot on, my wife’s California screaming bowl had everything she ordered but 1/3 of the bowl was onion, and mine was missing half of the ingredients. I ordered a carnitas verde burrito with no sour cream with the addition of fajita veggies. I started eating and only saw rice and pork. Figured they Taco Belled it and the ingredients weren’t mixed properly. When I was down to 1/2 of my burrito I finally hit my third internal ingredient...cheese. By the time I finished it I never found my fajita veggies, enchilada sauce, or my salsa. Shrug, at least the ingredients provided tasted good. Never going back.  Afterthought, if it was initially white rice and not Spanish rice then they added salsa or enchilada sauce. Still wouldn’t change my review from two stars. If I have to jump down the rabbit hole to contemplate burrito ingredients then...nope.
I tried the mango salad. Not bad!! The chicken pieces are fried. And that was a good thing.
I eat here at least once a week. Love their blackened fish crunchy tacos. Clean environment.. tables are separated due to covid. You can eat in and their restrooms are open to paying customers

Disgusting action by store employee with our order on 3 meals that we ordered 3 California Sunset with Taco Beef. California Tortilla Rockville Town Center employee put ground meat like pork instead of taco beef on 3 meals. We saw ground  greasy meat that we did not order. Unethical business!

Not particularly satisfied, unfortunately. My wife and I stopped by after receiving coupons in the mail. We ordered the Korean BBQ tacos and it did not taste anything like Korean BBQ. The sauce is quite diluted and watery, and the flavor is off the mark, sadly. The blackened fish is decent, relatively speaking.
Ran through the rain to get here from a parking garage, and it was worth it.
The queso is garbage

Got a bowl - it tasted great, seemed fresh, and was well priced with more meat and veggies than chipotle would give even if a little less food overall.  Chips and guac were disappointing though. Costs the same but less than half the guac compared to chipotle and tastes basically the same.

I tried this spot for the first time yesterday. I originally got this restaurant confused for Baja Fresh. Nevertheless, the ingredients were fresh and guacamole was nice and green (not browning). My only complaint is the meats... I ordered the Fajitas platter (not burrito) and the chicken and steak were NOT seasoned. In my opinion, in fajitas, the highlight of that meal is the meat. Not sure if it was over cooked or had been sitting out all day.  May need to just try a different location.

The best food in Rockville town center . I got the chicken nachos was so delicious. As I leave I asked for the manger and she came she was so sweet and respectful Samantha thanks for making me feel great while there I will be back for more .
Awesome spot to get food when in a hurry. The customer service is fast, pricing is fair, great character. Highly recommended
Great blackened fish tacos

I ordered a Fajita bowl. The rice was hard. ( It tasted like I was served what remained in the  warming bowl). After a few few bites, I informed the server's. They remade my order minus the Fajita vegetables. I was offered something else in place of the vegetables. The food wasn't great and over priced. I will not be dining at California Tortilla again.

Fantastic! One of the employees Garth made a simple mistake with my order today but fixed it really quick and efficiently and I really appreciated that. I was really satisfied with today’s visit to California Tortilla.  Amazing service, good food. Big shout-out to Garth

It was my first time coming to this location on our family's Taco Tuesday. I will not be back. While the price is right to feed a family of 3, we did not enjoy our dinner. I had fish tacos and a Southwestern salad. I will be calling in the morning to speak to the manager and to request a refund.🥺😥
Taco Tuesdays you get buy one get one free on tacos!

This place is hurting. Managers come and go. They have 4 people working, 1 in the back, 2 making food, and 1 at the register.  The online orders take huge chunks of their time while people actually standing there waiting for their lunch are waiting 15 minutes for their lunch order. This is ok since.people aren't going there because it takes so darn long to get cold food. It's also old and getting dingy. It's the only "fast" Mexican food in the town center.
They were out of multiple types of soda for their machine.  Kind of lame . Also , my daughter has been told that you don't get a cookie with kidsadlla . ?? Do or don't ?

The customer service is always prompt, great ambience, very nice employees. Will visit here again when I arrive here.

ordered chips and salsa and queso.  took them so long and the customer service was very rude. the place was a mess and they didn’t have ice in their soda machine. the salsa tasted awful and the chips were so stale. poorly cleaned bathrooms as well.
Great burritos
Great food at reasonable price.  Friendly workers.

This place was closed an HOUR before Google said it was closed. Whomever manages the GMB (Google My Business, which you should know because you're a business and have a Google listing) for this location needs to update it or tell the staff that works here to not close early. People want to eat here. If I could give zero stars based off my experience, I would. Very unprofessional for a business to close an hour early. Additionally, all other businesses in the area were still open. If you're planning on eating late, don't bother coming to this location because they close WAAAY earlier than they say they do. Very annoyed.
Enjoyed the food, the service, the atmosphere. The restroom need closest to the cashier needed attention.

This place offers terrible customer service! I was given attitude over them losing my order, as if it was my fault and I also had to involve my bank because they wouldn't give me a refund, they didn't even offer a replacement but either way I politely told them I couldn't wait because I had to return to work; however, I was treated poorly and they acted as if I was at fault. Even the manager is awful! you're better off taking your business somewhere else because if your order is not completely wrong they're just going to treat you disrespectfully.
So sad to show up at 810 pm and find the doors locked. Website etc state 9 pm closing.  Wouldnt have driven to the store had it been on the website that you close at 8.
Says on the door and on their website  that they close at 9 locked the door at 8 and said they were closed. Just a bit disappointed cause I swear I checked your hours.

The burritos are just huge. The service is a bit presumtuous and not the nost helpful attitude. Was surprised to have to pay a second bill for a soda; attendant hadnt bothered to ask about my wish for a drink. I had to ask. The place is clean and welcoming though.

Absolutely amazing, the food is so good!! and not only are there so many choices but all California tortilla restaurants have a huge wall of hot sauces, there's so many different kinds to choose from.  Interior is decent, half is booths and half is chairs.

I ordered a burrito and the chicken inside came out ice cold. I didn't eat it and the manager wouldn't let me get a refund, but only offered re-making the meal. I ended up walking down the street to Potbelly with a cold burrito-sized hole in my wallet.

Had to stop at the courthouse to get an ID, California Tortilla was right around the corner.  Clean resteraunt.  Staff was very helpful considering it was my first time here.  Got a bowl instead of a burrito.  Very tasty.  Upgraded with chips and a drink.  The queso was very good as well.  I would recomend stopping here.
Amazing food with a great variety. i would recommend. beware of rush hour its just that good.

Picked up food here.  Slow service at lunch for the number of people in the restaurant.  Food was a good. Also, you have to pay to park at this location.  They are very quick to give parking tickets even for a pick up order.

The only California  Tortilla that seems worth it to me is the one in Washington DC. The other two (the other one being in Bowie) are always dry and the cheese is never fresh

Count on water, or otherwise consider other options in Rockville until they fix the drink situation.
